{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":826,"text":"Puzzles"},{"time":2642,"text":"and magic."},{"time":4941,"text":"I work in what most people think"},{"time":7085,"text":"are two distinct fields,"},{"time":9523,"text":"but I believe they are the same."},{"time":12594,"text":"I am both a magician and"},{"time":14570,"text":"a New York Times crossword puzzle constructor,"},{"time":18406,"text":"which basically means I've taken"},{"time":19770,"text":"the world's two nerdiest hobbies"},{"time":21392,"text":"and combined them into one career."},{"time":24320,"text":"And I believe that magic and puzzles are the same"},{"time":27443,"text":"because they both key into one of"},{"time":29379,"text":"the most important human drives:"},{"time":32030,"text":"the urge to solve."},{"time":34116,"text":"Human beings are wired to solve,"},{"time":37249,"text":"to make order out of chaos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":40253,"text":"It's certainly true for me."},{"time":41760,"text":"I've been solving my whole life."},{"time":43599,"text":"High school consisted of epic\nScrabble matches in the cafeteria"},{"time":47903,"text":"and not really talking to girls,"},{"time":49612,"text":"and then at about that time"},{"time":51435,"text":"I started learning magic tricks"},{"time":53130,"text":"and definitely not talking to girls."},{"time":55597,"text":"There's nothing like starting a conversation with,"},{"time":57644,"text":"\"Hey, did you know that 'prestidigitation' is worth"},{"time":60200,"text":"20 points in Scrabble?\""},{"time":63224,"text":"But back then, I noticed an intersection"},{"time":66011,"text":"between puzzles and illusion."},{"time":68736,"text":"When you do the crossword puzzle"},{"time":70682,"text":"or when you watch a magic show,"},{"time":72628,"text":"you become a solver,"},{"time":74880,"text":"and your goal is to try to find the order in the chaos,"},{"time":78658,"text":"the chaos of, say, a black-and-white puzzle grid,"},{"time":81898,"text":"a mixed-up bag of Scrabble tiles,"},{"time":84042,"text":"or a shuffled pack of playing cards."},{"time":86850,"text":"And today, as a cruciverbalist —"},{"time":89864,"text":"23 points —"},{"time":91450,"text":"and an illusion designer, I create that chaos."},{"time":95207,"text":"I test your ability to solve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":98552,"text":"Now, it turns out research tells us"},{"time":100962,"text":"that solving is as primal as eating and sleeping."},{"time":104960,"text":"From birth, we are wired to solve."},{"time":108695,"text":"In one UCLA study, newborns still in the hospital"},{"time":112532,"text":"were shown patterns, patterns like this:"},{"time":115220,"text":"circle, cross, circle, cross."},{"time":118831,"text":"And then the pattern was changed: triangle, square."},{"time":123150,"text":"And by tracking an infant's gaze,"},{"time":125806,"text":"we know that newborns as young as a day old"},{"time":129110,"text":"can notice and respond to disruptions in order."},{"time":131722,"text":"It's remarkable."},{"time":133140,"text":"So from infancy through old age,"},{"time":135738,"text":"the urge to solve unites us all,"},{"time":138110,"text":"and I even found this photo on Instagram"},{"time":140750,"text":"of pop star Katy Perry solving a crossword puzzle"},{"time":143904,"text":"with her morning coffee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146130,"text":"Like."},{"time":147801,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151669,"text":"Now, solving exists across all cultures."},{"time":156210,"text":"The American invention is the crossword puzzle,"},{"time":159154,"text":"and this year we are celebrating"},{"time":160553,"text":"the 100th anniversary of the crossword puzzle,"},{"time":163226,"text":"first published in The New York World."},{"time":165733,"text":"But many other cultures have\ntheir signature puzzles as well."},{"time":168372,"text":"China gives us tangrams,"},{"time":170382,"text":"which would test solvers' abilities"},{"time":172427,"text":"to form shapes from the jumbled pieces."},{"time":175567,"text":"Chaos. Order."},{"time":178570,"text":"Order."},{"time":180628,"text":"And order."},{"time":183823,"text":"That one's my favorite, let's hear it again."},{"time":186393,"text":"Okay."},{"time":188064,"text":"And how about this puzzle"},{"time":189840,"text":"invented in 18th-century England:"},{"time":192279,"text":"the jigsaw puzzle."},{"time":194330,"text":"Is this not making order out of chaos?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":198144,"text":"So as you can see,"},{"time":199613,"text":"we are always solving."},{"time":201392,"text":"We are always trying to decode our world."},{"time":205354,"text":"It's an eternal quest."},{"time":206884,"text":"It's just like the one Cervantes wrote about"},{"time":209528,"text":"in \"Don Quixote,\""},{"time":210979,"text":"which by the way is the root of the word \"quixotry,\""},{"time":212981,"text":"the highest-scoring Scrabble word of all time,"},{"time":214804,"text":"365 points."},{"time":216660,"text":"But anyway, \"Don Quixote\" is an important book."},{"time":219877,"text":"You guys have read \"Don Quixote,\" yes?"},{"time":221914,"text":"I'm seeing some heads nod."},{"time":223420,"text":"Come on guys, really?"},{"time":224702,"text":"Who's read \"Don Quixote?\" Let's do this.\nRaise your hands if you've read \"Don Quixote.\""},{"time":227239,"text":"There we go. Smart audience."},{"time":228349,"text":"Who's read \"Don Quixote?\" Get them up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230063,"text":"Okay, good, because I need somebody smart here"},{"time":234276,"text":"because now I'm going to demonstrate"},{"time":235478,"text":"with the help of one of you"},{"time":237350,"text":"just how deeply rooted your urge to solve is,"},{"time":240686,"text":"just how wired to solve all of you really are,"},{"time":243185,"text":"so I'm going to come into the audience"},{"time":244627,"text":"and find somebody to help me."},{"time":247625,"text":"Let's see."},{"time":249747,"text":"Everybody's looking away all of a sudden."},{"time":253639,"text":"Can I? Would you? What is your name? Gwen."},{"time":257556,"text":"I'm not a mind reader, I can see your name tag."},{"time":259997,"text":"Come with me, Gwen. Everyone give her \na round of applause, make her feel welcome."},{"time":264310,"text":"Gwen, after you."},{"time":265982,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":267864,"text":"Are you so excited?"},{"time":271275,"text":"Did you know that your name is worth"},{"time":272730,"text":"eight points in Scrabble?"},{"time":274328,"text":"Okay, stand right here, Gwen, right here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278615,"text":"Now, Gwen, before we begin,"},{"time":281117,"text":"I'd like to point out a piece of the puzzle,"},{"time":283726,"text":"which is here in this envelope,"},{"time":285263,"text":"and I will not go near it. Okay?"},{"time":286883,"text":"And over here we have a\ndrawing of some farm animals."},{"time":288891,"text":"You can see we have an owl, we have a horse,"},{"time":290251,"text":"a donkey, a rooster, an ox, and a sheep,"},{"time":292480,"text":"and then here, Gwen, we have"},{"time":293690,"text":"some fancy art store markers,"},{"time":296110,"text":"colors like, can you see that word right there?"},{"time":298450,"text":"Gwen: Cobalt.\nDavid Kwong: Cobalt, yes. Cobalt."},{"time":300789,"text":"But we have a silver, a red, an emerald,"},{"time":303407,"text":"and an amber marker,"},{"time":304865,"text":"and Gwen, you are going to color this drawing"},{"time":307130,"text":"just like you were five years old,"},{"time":308607,"text":"one marker at a time."},{"time":309715,"text":"It's going to be a lot of fun."},{"time":311234,"text":"But I'm going to go over here."},{"time":312255,"text":"I don't want to see what you're doing."},{"time":314342,"text":"Okay, so don't start yet."},{"time":315412,"text":"Wait for me to get over here and close my eyes."},{"time":316839,"text":"Now Gwen, are you ready?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":318717,"text":"Pick up just one marker, pick up just one marker,"},{"time":322227,"text":"and why don't you color in the horse for me?"},{"time":323612,"text":"Color in the horse — big, big, big scribbles,"},{"time":327165,"text":"broad strokes, don't worry about staying in the lines."},{"time":330123,"text":"All right. Great."},{"time":331399,"text":"And why don't you take that marker and recap it"},{"time":332975,"text":"and place it on the table for me."},{"time":334905,"text":"Okay, and pick up another marker out of the cup"},{"time":338125,"text":"and take off the cap"},{"time":340575,"text":"and color in the donkey for me, color in the donkey."},{"time":342641,"text":"Big scribbles."},{"time":345709,"text":"Okay, cool, and re-cap that marker"},{"time":347943,"text":"and place it on the table."},{"time":349445,"text":"And pick up another marker for me"},{"time":351723,"text":"and take off the cap. Isn't this fun?"},{"time":354186,"text":"And color in the owl for me."},{"time":355513,"text":"Color in the owl."},{"time":358564,"text":"Okay, and recap that marker"},{"time":361050,"text":"and pick up another marker out of the cup"},{"time":362838,"text":"and color in the rooster for me, color in the rooster."},{"time":366414,"text":"Good, good, good, good, good."},{"time":367838,"text":"Big, big, big strokes. Good, good."},{"time":368931,"text":"Pick up another marker out of the cup"},{"time":371196,"text":"and color in the ox for me. Color in the ox."},{"time":374693,"text":"Okay, good."},{"time":375956,"text":"A lot of color on that, and recap,\nand place it on the table,"},{"time":378406,"text":"and pick up another marker out of the cup."},{"time":381110,"text":"Oh, I'm out? Okay, I'm going to turn around."},{"time":383849,"text":"Did I forget? Oh, I forgot my purple marker."},{"time":389109,"text":"This is still going to work, though."},{"time":390452,"text":"I think this is still going to work, mostly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392735,"text":"So Gwen, I'm going to hand you this envelope."},{"time":395888,"text":"Don't open it yet. Do not open it yet,"},{"time":398840,"text":"but I am going to write down your choices"},{"time":401231,"text":"so that everybody can see"},{"time":403390,"text":"the choices that you made."},{"time":404663,"text":"Okay, great. So we have a cobalt horse,"},{"time":413046,"text":"amber owl,"},{"time":418452,"text":"a silver ox,"},{"time":423233,"text":"yes, okay, a red donkey,"},{"time":426675,"text":"and what was the emerald color? A rooster."},{"time":430050,"text":"An emerald rooster. Okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434120,"text":"Now for the moment of truth, Gwen,"},{"time":436286,"text":"we're going to take a look in that envelope."},{"time":437971,"text":"Why don't you open it up and remove"},{"time":439886,"text":"the one piece of paper from inside"},{"time":441178,"text":"and hand it to me,"},{"time":442207,"text":"and we will see if it matches your choices."},{"time":446910,"text":"Yes, I think it does."},{"time":448345,"text":"We have a cobalt horse, we have a red donkey,"},{"time":449909,"text":"we have an amber owl, we have\nan emerald rooster, a silver ox,"},{"time":452206,"text":"I forgot my purple marker so we have a blank sheep,"},{"time":454217,"text":"but that's a pretty amazing\ncoincidence, don't you think?"},{"time":456932,"text":"Gwen, well done. That's beautiful. (Applause)"},{"time":461113,"text":"I'll take that back from you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":462880,"text":"So ladies and gentlemen, how is this possible?"},{"time":466744,"text":"How is this possible? Well, could it be"},{"time":469561,"text":"that Gwen's brain is so wired to solve"},{"time":473823,"text":"that she decoded hidden messages?"},{"time":476669,"text":"Well this is the puzzle I present to you."},{"time":478716,"text":"Could there be order"},{"time":480696,"text":"in the chaos that I created?"},{"time":483700,"text":"Let's take a closer look."},{"time":485440,"text":"Do you recall when I showed you these puzzle pieces?"},{"time":489451,"text":"What image did it ultimately become? A cobalt horse."},{"time":495208,"text":"The plot thickens."},{"time":496985,"text":"And then we played a game of tangrams"},{"time":499190,"text":"with an emerald rooster."},{"time":504180,"text":"That one's my favorite."},{"time":506378,"text":"And then we had an experiment with a silver ox."},{"time":512633,"text":"And Katy Perry drinks her morning coffee"},{"time":515333,"text":"out of an amber owl."},{"time":519162,"text":"Thank you, Katy, for taking that photo for me."},{"time":520841,"text":"Oh, and there's one more, there's one more."},{"time":522806,"text":"I believe you colored a red donkey, Gwen."},{"time":526234,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, could you raise your hands"},{"time":527864,"text":"for me if you've read \"Don Quixote?\""},{"time":530284,"text":"Who's read \"Don Quixote?\" (Laughter)"},{"time":533179,"text":"But wait, but wait, wait, wait, wait, there's more."},{"time":534955,"text":"There's more."},{"time":536450,"text":"Gwen, I was so confident"},{"time":539209,"text":"that you were going to make these choices"},{"time":541133,"text":"that I made another prediction,"},{"time":543771,"text":"and I put it in an even more indelible place,"},{"time":547101,"text":"and it's right here."},{"time":549519,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":550801,"text":"we have today's New York Times."},{"time":554379,"text":"The date is March 18th, 2014."},{"time":558204,"text":"Many of you in the first couple of rows"},{"time":560050,"text":"have it underneath your seats as well."},{"time":562170,"text":"Really dig. We hid them under there."},{"time":564380,"text":"See if you can fish out the newspaper"},{"time":565921,"text":"and open up to the arts section"},{"time":568319,"text":"and you will find the crossword puzzle,"},{"time":571782,"text":"and the crossword puzzle today"},{"time":573345,"text":"was written by yours truly."},{"time":575404,"text":"You can see my name above the grid."},{"time":576470,"text":"I'm going to give this to you, Gwen, to take a look."},{"time":579003,"text":"And I will also put it up on the screen."},{"time":583196,"text":"Now let's take a look"},{"time":585078,"text":"at another piece of the puzzle."},{"time":588385,"text":"If you look at the first clue for 1-across,"},{"time":591603,"text":"it starts with the letter C, for corrupt,"},{"time":594899,"text":"and just below that we have an O, for outfielder,"},{"time":597825,"text":"and if you keep reading the\nfirst letters of the clues down,"},{"time":600771,"text":"you get cobalt horse,"},{"time":603572,"text":"amber owl, silver ox,"},{"time":607060,"text":"red donkey, and emerald rooster."},{"time":610558,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":612164,"text":"That's pretty cool, right?"},{"time":617735,"text":"It's The New York Times."},{"time":619446,"text":"But wait, wait, wait, wait. Wait."},{"time":621022,"text":"Oh, Gwen,"},{"time":622544,"text":"do you recall how I forgot my purple marker,"},{"time":625148,"text":"and you were unable to color the sheep?"},{"time":628195,"text":"Well, if you keep reading"},{"time":629648,"text":"starting with 25-down,"},{"time":631279,"text":"it says,"},{"time":632185,"text":"\"Oh, by the way,"},{"time":633958,"text":"the sheep can be left blank.\""},{"time":638270,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":642706,"text":"But wait, wait, wait, there's one more thing,"},{"time":644280,"text":"there's one more thing,"},{"time":645483,"text":"there's one final piece of the puzzle."},{"time":648322,"text":"Gwen, I am so grateful for your choices"},{"time":652641,"text":"because if we take a look"},{"time":654632,"text":"at the first letters of your combinations,"},{"time":656863,"text":"we get \"C-H-A-O-S\" for chaos"},{"time":659875,"text":"and \"O-R-D-E-R\" for order."},{"time":662698,"text":"That's chaos and order."},{"time":664228,"text":"We've all made order out of chaos."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665904,"text":"So ladies and gentlemen, the next time"},{"time":667907,"text":"you find yourself with a puzzle,"},{"time":669459,"text":"whether it's in your life or in your work,"},{"time":672501,"text":"or maybe it's at the Sunday morning"},{"time":673682,"text":"breakfast table with The New York Times,"},{"time":676090,"text":"remember, you are all wired to solve."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679932,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681524,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}